metadata.name: Cubick (Neon Red) #15
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender Renders.

The variations are best viewed in live mode.

In each output, the four "cubes" are arranged in the same calming, 'zen-like' formation.

In each output, the orientation of the "cubes", and the number and positions of the colored regions varies.

All outputs in this collection will have the same color palette (called Neon Red).

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1375x1500px PNG.

Several "Cubick" collections will be released, each with a different color palette.

metadata.name: brushstroke #81
metadata.description:
Brushstroke is an algorithm to form a minimal, modern, artistic paint on a canvas. It mimics a painter's hand gesture to apply different types of strokes. Those strokes may vary from thin straight lines to fat curvy arcs. The direction of the strokes may change for each stroke or not. There may be an excessive amount of them as there may be just several. Strokes may intersect and form a group. It generates color palettes as an artist does. There are more than twenty parameters that give variety to pieces. 

Brushstroke is built on the p5.js library. As a way of saying thanks, you will contribute to the Processing Foundation by collecting this work.

metadata.name: Blueprints of balance #58
metadata.description:
Balance in art is one of the basic principles of design, along with contrast, movement, rhythm, emphasis, pattern, unity, and variety. Balance refers to how the elements of art (line, shape, color, value, space, form, texture) relate to each other within the composition in terms of their visual weight to create visual equilibrium. That is, one side does not seem heavier than another.

But there is no balance without Chaos. And that is why for one hour everyday each Blueprint of balance let it go and turns into its alternative wild version.

metadata.name: Pine Dream #59
metadata.description:
Pine dream by Asaf Slook (2022)

This work is an attempt to create a simple pen-like generated drawing, in a way that confuses the observer to perceive it to be a real unique hand-drawn piece.

Rare features:
- Lonely tree
- Static stroke
- Sunny day palette
- Dotted land
- Partial land
 
The best results are from 1000x1000 and above.

This work was created using p5.js and love :)

metadata.name: Terrain #9
metadata.description:
Some landscapes are serene, others phenomenal.

The control points of a polygonal Bezier curve rotate while the entire polygon expands and contracts, leaving a trajectory.
Royalties on secondary sales include donations to the Processing Foundation.

Enjoy in full screen.
